[3]
Date: Mon 17 Oct 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Macedonia Press Agency, 17 Oct 2005 [edited]
<http://www.mpa.gr/article.html?doc_id=550234>

Tests on dead birds in Evros
-----------------------------
3 dead birds found in Evros, northeastern Greece, were sent for tests at
the Thessaloniki Veterinary Laboratory. 2 of the birds were found in
Orestiada and one in Soufli.
The EU Foreign Ministers meet in Luxembourg tomorrow [18 Oct 2005], while
EU veterinarians call for stronger measures in addition to the banning of
the imports of poultry and poultry products from Romania, where bird
culling continues to avert the spread of the disease.
The Serb Health Minister expressed support for the initiative undertaken by
Greek Health Minister Nikitas Kaklamanis for a meeting of the Balkan and
Black Sea countries.
Samples of migratory birds continue to be taken in Evros after the bird flu
cases recorded in Romania and Turkey.
During the weekend [15-16 October 2005], the Veterinary Department at the
Prefecture of Evros in cooperation with the Hunting Association of
Alexandroupolis collected 20 more samples of migratory birds to be sent for
tests to the Thessaloniki Veterinary Laboratory, while the results from the
tests conducted on the 1st 40 samples of migratory birds sent 5 days ago
will be out before the end of the week [3rd week October 2005].
